lean on me (song).comment: Oh yeah, Lean on Me. That's such a classic. It was written and recorded by Bill Withers in 1972 and it was inducted into the Grammy Hall of Fame in 2015.

the long and winding road.comment: Oh yeah, The Long and Winding Road! That Beatles song is so iconic! It was the last song they recorded together before they split up, right?

let's get it started.comment: Oh yeah! I know that one, it was a hit for the Black Eyed Peas back in 2004.

sweet home alabama.comment: Oh yeah, I know that one! It's a classic rock song by Lynyrd Skynyrd released in 1974. It's all about a man who has left his home and is trying to make his way back.

fame (david bowie song).comment: Yeah, Fame is such a classic! I love when Bowie sings the chorus "Fame, what you like is in the limelight".

smalltown boy.comment: Oh yeah, I love Smalltown Boy too! The song is about a young man who is rejected by his family and small town for being different and then goes out to make his own way in the world.

a whole new world.comment: Oh yeah! A Whole New World is such a beautiful song. It was written by Alan Menken and Tim Rice for the 1992 Disney movie Aladdin.

redbone (song).comment: Oh yeah, Redbone by Childish Gambino! That's a great song. It was released in 2016 and was nominated for Record of the Year at the 2018 Grammy Awards.

say something (kylie minogue song).comment: Oh yeah! That's such a great song. I love the way it has a soulful sound mixed with a funky dance beat.

the wreck of the edmund fitzgerald.wiki_doc_title: The Wreck of the Edmund Fitzgerald
the wreck of the edmund fitzgerald.comment: Wow, I love that song too! It was released in 1976 and is about the sinking of a freighter ship in Lake Superior, right?

dancing in the dark (bruce springsteen s.wiki_doc_title: Dancing in the Dark (Bruce Springsteen song)
dancing in the dark (bruce springsteen s.comment: Oh yeah, I love that song! It's off Bruce's Born in the U.S.A. album and it's about the struggles of everyday life.

rasputin (song).comment: Wow, Rasputin is such a classic! It was released in 1978 by the Russian band Boney M and it was a massive hit in Europe.

night changes.comment: Oh yeah, Night Changes by One Direction? That's a great song! I love the way the chorus builds up and then breaks into a softer melody.

peaches (justin bieber song).comment: Oh yeah, I've heard of that one. It's a really sweet song about how his wife is the perfect person for him.

castle on the hill.comment: Oh yeah, Castle on the Hill by Ed Sheeran! It's a nostalgic song about his childhood and growing up in his hometown.

back to december.comment: Wow, I love Back to December too! It's a great song by Taylor Swift, right? It's all about reflection and regret and how sometimes its better to look back and learn from the past.

payphone (song).comment: I love Payphone too! It's so catchy and has that easy-listening feel to it. I always belt out the chorus when it comes on the radio.

there's nothing holdin' me back.comment: Oh, I love that song! I think it's so uplifting, especially the chorus when Shawn Mendes sings "There's nothing holding me back!" It always gives me a boost of confidence.

treat you better (shawn mendes song).comment: Wow, I love that song too! It's got such a great melody and meaningful lyrics. My favourite part is when he sings "I know I can treat you better than he can". It's such a powerful line!

flowers (miley cyrus song).comment: Wow, that's a great song! I love the upbeat melody and the lyrics about self-love!

anti-hero (song).comment: Wow, I love that song too! It's from Taylor Swift's album Midnights. Taylor said that it was actually her favorite song from the album!

creepin' (metro boomin, the weeknd and 2.wiki_doc_title: Creepin' (Metro Boomin, the Weeknd and 21 Savage song)
creepin' (metro boomin, the weeknd and 2.comment: Oh yeah! I totally love that song too. It's so catchy and the beat is really cool. I love the way 21 Savage's verse adds a different dynamic to the track. It's definitely one of my favourites!

kill bill (sza song).comment: Oh, I love that song too! It's so chill and soulful. The lyrics are so powerful and it's definitely one of my go-to's when I need to relax. Plus, I love the way SZA sings it!

money (lisa song).comment: Oh, I love that song! I think it's so cool how a concert hall can go into silent when Lisa sings 'Everyone silent, listen to my money talk'.
